<div type="definition">
<p>INVITED VISITOR FROM a DIFFERENT PLACE OR FAMILY IN-RELATION-TO someone in whose PLACE S/HE BE-IN:is in.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general neutral word for a guest is kè 客 (ant. zhǔ 主 "host"), but this word is also used to refer to strangers.</p>
<p>2. Bīn 賓 (ant. zhǔ 主 "host") is an honorific term for an honoured guest.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006 HUMAN AFFAIRS 42.</p>
<p>賓，尊貴的客人。</p>
<p>客，客人的通稱。</p>
        </div>
